{
  "info": {
    "name": "Qualiphy API",
    "description": "Qualiphy telemedicine API.\n\n## Getting started in 30 seconds\n\n1. Click the collection name above → **Variables** tab → paste your `api_key` value (find it in your Qualiphy dashboard → Settings).\n2. Hit **Save**.\n3. Open **Exam → List exams** and click **Send**. You should get a 200 with your exam list.\n4. Now run **Create exam invite** — it auto-pulls an `exam_id` from the previous response and fires a test-mode invite.\n5. Subsequent requests (resend, cancel, submit answers, upload attachment) auto-pull the `patient_exam_id` from the invite response.\n\n## Auth\n\nEvery request body **MUST** include an `api_key` field (no headers, no query params). All endpoints are POST with `Content-Type: application/json`. Base URL defaults to `https://api.qualiphy.me`.\n\n## Auto-chaining\n\nThe Tests script on each request captures useful response IDs into collection variables, so you do not need to copy-paste between requests:\n\n- `/exam_list` → sets `{{exam_id}}` from `exams[0].id`\n- `/exam_invite` → sets `{{patient_id}}` from `patient_exams[0].patient_exam_id` and `{{meeting_uuid}}` from `meeting_uuid`\n- `/partner_pharmacy_list` → sets `{{pharmacy_id}}` from `pharmacies[0].pharmacy_id`\n- `/partner_pharmacy_treatment_packages` → sets `{{order_set_id}}` from `treatment_packages[0].order_set_id`\n- `/custom_pharmacy_search` → sets `{{ncpdpid}}` from `pharmacies[0].ncpdpid`\n\nCheck the Postman console (View → Show Postman Console) after firing any request to see which variables it set.\n\n## Field-name gotchas\n\n- `patient_exam_id` (per-patient) vs `exam_id` (exam type) — they are different. Resend / cancel / upload use `patient_exam_id`.\n- `custom_pharmacy`: 1 = Custom, 2 = Partner. Inverted from what you would expect.\n- `phone_number` not `phone`.\n- Legacy `exam_pos_id` is still returned alongside `order_set_id` for older integrations.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_postman_id": "qualiphy-api-1-0-0"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Exam",
      "description": "Patient exam invites and lifecycle endpoints.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List exams (/api/exam_list)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  try {",
                  "    const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (j && Array.isArray(j.exams) && j.exams.length > 0 && j.exams[0].id != null) {",
                  "      pm.collectionVariables.set('exam_id', String(j.exams[0].id));",
                  "      console.log('[auto-chain] exam_id =', j.exams[0].id);",
                  "    }",
                  "  } catch (e) { console.warn('[auto-chain] exam_list parse failed:', e); }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/exam_list",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "exam_list"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"api_key\": \"{{api_key}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "Returns every exam configured on your clinic. Use this to discover the `id` values you pass to `/exam_invite`. Each exam record includes `rx_type` (1=GFE, 2=Rx), `attachments_required`, `attachments`, and a preset `price` if configured.\n\n**Auto-chain**: this request's Tests script captures `exams[0].id` into `{{exam_id}}` so subsequent requests work without manual paste."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 - typical exam list",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/exam_list",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "exam_list"]
                },
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"api_key\": \"{{api_key}}\"\n}",
                  "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
                }
              },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "cookie": [],
              "body": "{\n  \"clinic_id\": 1234,\n  \"exams\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": 2228,\n      \"title\": \"Embrace Aging GFE (Dermal Fillers, Botox, PDO, Microneedling PRP)\",\n      \"rx_type\": 1,\n      \"price\": null,\n      \"attachments_required\": 1,\n      \"attachments\": []\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2769,\n      \"title\": \"3 Month Supply: Semaglutide with Medication Shipping (No Labwork Required)\",\n      \"rx_type\": 2,\n      \"price\": null,\n      \"attachments_required\": 2,\n      \"attachments\": [\"ID\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 1486,\n      \"title\": \"Urgent Care - Acne (Doxycycline, Clindamycin, Benzoyl Peroxide) Treatment\",\n      \"rx_type\": 2,\n      \"price\": null,\n      \"attachments_required\": 2,\n      \"attachments\": [\"ID\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Create exam invite (/api/exam_invite)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  try {",
                  "    const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (j && Array.isArray(j.patient_exams) && j.patient_exams.length > 0 && j.patient_exams[0].patient_exam_id != null) {",
                  "      pm.collectionVariables.set('patient_id', String(j.patient_exams[0].patient_exam_id));",
                  "      console.log('[auto-chain] patient_id =', j.patient_exams[0].patient_exam_id);",
                  "    }",
                  "    if (j && j.meeting_uuid) {",
                  "      pm.collectionVariables.set('meeting_uuid', String(j.meeting_uuid));",
                  "      console.log('[auto-chain] meeting_uuid =', j.meeting_uuid);",
                  "    }",
                  "  } catch (e) { console.warn('[auto-chain] exam_invite parse failed:', e); }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/exam_invite",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "exam_invite"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"api_key\": \"{{api_key}}\",\n  \"exams\": [{{exam_id}}],\n  \"first_name\": \"Test\",\n  \"last_name\": \"Approve\",\n  \"email\": \"test@example.com\",\n  \"dob\": \"1990-06-30\",\n  \"phone_number\": \"+15555550100\",\n  \"state\": \"TE\",\n  \"tele_state\": \"TE\",\n  \"webhook_url\": \"{{webhook_url}}\",\n  \"additional_data\": \"{\\\"order_id\\\":\\\"WC-12847\\\"}\",\n  \"redirect_approve\": \"https://yourstore.com/cleared\",\n  \"redirect_reject\": \"https://yourstore.com/needs-followup\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "Core endpoint. Creates a patient exam invite, returns a meeting URL, and (by default) emails and texts the patient. This example uses test-mode routing (`state` and `tele_state` set to TE) so it is safe to fire as-is. For Rx flows, add `pharmacy_id` + `order_set_id` (partner pharmacy) or `custom_pharmacy: 1` + `ncpdpid` + custom-pharmacy address fields. Watch the `custom_pharmacy` mapping — 1=Custom, 2=Partner.\n\n**Auto-chain**: this request's Tests script captures `patient_exams[0].patient_exam_id` into `{{patient_id}}` and `meeting_uuid` into `{{meeting_uuid}}`."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 - invite created",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/exam_invite",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "exam_invite"]
                },
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"api_key\": \"{{api_key}}\",\n  \"exams\": [4226],\n  \"first_name\": \"Test\",\n  \"last_name\": \"Approve\",\n  \"email\": \"test@example.com\",\n  \"dob\": \"1990-06-30\",\n  \"phone_number\": \"+15555550100\",\n  \"state\": \"TE\",\n  \"tele_state\": \"TE\"\n}",
                  "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
                }
              },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "cookie": [],
              "body": "{\n  \"http_code\": 200,\n  \"meeting_url\": \"https://app.qualiphy.me/meeting/abc-123-def-456\",\n  \"meeting_uuid\": \"abc-123-def-456\",\n  \"patient_exams\": [\n    {\n      \"patient_exam_id\": 4844,\n      \"exam_title\": \"GFE Aesthetic\",\n      \"exam_id\": 4226\n    }\n  ]\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "401 - unauthorized",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/exam_invite",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "exam_invite"]
                },
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"api_key\": \"BAD_KEY\",\n  \"exams\": [4226]\n}",
                  "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
                }
