              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "REFERENCE ONLY — DO NOT SEND.\n\nQualiphy POSTs lifecycle events to your `webhook_url`. Your handler should respond 200 immediately and process asynchronously.\n\nDispatch on `event`:\n\n- **event=1 Consultation Complete**. Fires for every exam (GFE, Rx, Urgent Care). `exam_status` is one of: Approved, Rejected, Deferred to Medical Director, NA, Missed. `exam_url` is a CloudFront-hosted signed PDF — mirror to your own storage if you need long-term access.\n\n- **event=2 Prescription Confirmed**. Fires only for Rx exams after event 1. Carries `prescription[]` (each item: drug_name, dosage_form_type, strength, size, quantity, directions, duration_days, refill_amount, ndc_number, schedule_code, pharmacy_name, pharmacy_contacts[], prescription_tracking[], created_at), `prescribed_os_id`, and the full consultation envelope.\n\n- **event=3 Prescription Tracking**. Fires only when a partner pharmacy ships. Carries `patient_exam_id`, `prescription_id`, `tracking_number`, `delivery_service`, `pharmacy_location`, `order_id`. Custom-pharmacy flows never get event 3.\n\nThis example shows an event=1 Approved payload. The saved 'examples' tab on this request includes event=2 and event=3 payloads."
